h crude bone-axes and move with unnatural speed. Your Turn (Player Action): 1. **Engage with the Steam-Pistol:** Fire your modified steam-pistol at the lead Cultist to create a path for escape. 2. **Use the Uzman Wrench:** Drop the pistol and charge, relying on the sheer mass and momentum of your heavy wrench to repel the initial assault. 3. **Flee Backwards:** Attempt to retreat back toward the entrance, abandoning the immediate objective to gain solid ground. </s> [INST] 1. Engage with the Steam-Pistol: Fire your modified steam-pistol at the lead Cultist to create a path for escape. [/INST] <s> **Narrator:** You choose to **Engage with the Steam-Pistol**. You lift the heavy, brass weapon, its pressure gauge hissing furiously. You squeeze the trigger, sending a superheated jet of steam and scrap metal directly into the chest of the lead Cultist. [SYSTEM: [ROLL LOG: Attack Roll: 9/10. **Critical Hit.** Instant incapacitation.]] The impact is horrific; the cultist\u2019s ribs collapse inward with a wet *crack*, and they sink silently into the mire. The other two, however, are undeterred\u2014they shriek and close the distance, one lunging for your legs, the other swinging a bone-axe high. Your Turn (Player Action): 1. **Pistol Whip:** Smash the steam-pistol's heavy stock into the face of the Cultist swinging the axe. 2. **Kick the Attacker:** Use your heavy boot to punt the Cultist lunging for your legs into the deep sludge. 3. **Emergency Release Valve:** Open a non-standard release valve on your armor, jetting a noxious cloud of pressurized, hot oil into the confined space (risk of self-injury/weapon damage). </s> [INST] both pistol whip and kick the other attacker one after the other in rapid succession [/INST] <s> **Narrator:** You attempt a brutal combination, swinging the heavy stock of the steam-pistol at the axe-wielding Cultist while simultaneously using your powerful, sludge-encrusted boot to **Kick the Attacker** diving low. [SYSTEM: [ROLL LOG: Melee Combat Check: 6/10. **Success.** Both targets repelled.]] The pistol stock connects with a sickening crunch, shattering the jaw of the axe-wielder, who stumbles back howling. Your kick connects squarely with the second Cultist's torso, sending them sliding back across the slick tunnel floor, momentarily dazed. You have bought yourself a critical few seconds of space. You are still deep in the sludge, however, and the schematics are further in. Your Turn (Player Action): 1. **Advance and Finish:** Charge forward and execute the two stunned Cultists before they recover. 2. **Press the Advantage:** Ignore the stunned foes and immediately run deeper into the tunnel toward the objective. 3. **Barricade:** Use the wreckage of the first slain Cultist and some loose pipe to try and barricade the side fissure they emerged from. </s> [INST] execute, barricade and then charge forward [/INST] <s> **Narrator:** The sludge environment makes performing three complex actions in rapid succession extremely dangerous, but you prioritize eliminating the threat before securing the path. You choose to **Execute** the two stunned Cultists. You bring your Uzman Wrench down twice, the first blow silencing the axe-wielder, the second crushing the skull of the low-attacker. *Purged.* With no time to waste, you rapidly attempt to **Barricade** the fissure, hauling a heavy piece of piping and the remains of the first Cultist's body into the opening. [SYSTEM: [ROLL LOG: Efficiency Check: 5/10. **Partial Success.** The barricade is messy but slows egress.]] Finally, you **Charge Forward**, splashing heavily through the mire. The tunnel opens into a large, partially submerged maintenance bay. You locate the schematics\u2014a heavy, sealed data-slate\u2014resting on a rusted workstation above the water line. However, the movement of your charge has roused something far larger in the flooded depths. The water line ripples and a massive, mottled eye, the size of your fist, opens in the gloom. This is a **Mire-Gorgon**, a mutated predator of the swamp. Your Turn (Player Action): 1. **Grab the Schematics and Retreat:** Snatch the data-slate and immediately turn back, trying to outrun the Gorgon in the narrow tunnel. 2. **Engage the Gorgon:** Use your steam-pistol on the Gorgon's exposed eye before it can fully emerge. 3. **Sacrifice Kit:** Jettison a heavy piece of non-essential equipment (like your spare parts bag) into the water as a distraction before grabbing the slate. </s> [INST] 3. Sacrifice Kit: Jettison a heavy piece of non-essential equipment (like your spare parts bag) into the water as a distraction before grabbing the slate. [/INST] <s> **Narrator:** You choose to **Sacrifice Kit**. With a desperate urgency, you unclip your heavy, oil-saturated spare parts bag\u2014a full 10 kilos of brass fittings and scrap\u2014and hurl it into the water near the Gorgon's position. The predator reacts instantly, its huge, rubbery mouth snapping down on the heavy metal object with an audible crunch, momentarily confusing its hunting drive. [SYSTEM: [ROLL LOG: Diversion Check: 8/10. **Success.** Gorgon distracted.]] You seize the critical moment. You snatch the **data-slate** from the workstation, its smooth, cold surface confirming the recovery of the schematics. You turn and plunge back into the sludge-filled tunnel system, moving as fast as your heavy Uzman armor allows. Behind you, the Gorgon gives a deep, rumbling cry of frustration, realizing the deception. You can hear its vast body beginning to drag itself out of the water and into the tunnel. Your Turn (Player Action): 1. **Trigger the Barricade:** Fire a final blast from your steam-pistol at the makeshift barricade, hoping to collapse the loose pipes and rubble to momentarily slow the pursuit. 2. **Continue Retreat:** Trust your speed and the Mire's density to slow the creature, focusing only on getting back to the surface exit. 3. **Use Wrench as Prop:** Drive your heavy Uzman Wrench into the floor of the tunnel and use it as an anchor point to briefly rest and recover stamina (Risk of being overtaken). </s> [INST] 1. Trigger the Barricade: Fire a final blast from your steam-pistol at the makeshift barricade, hoping to collapse the loose pipes and rubble to momentarily slow the pursuit. 2. Continue Retreat: Trust your speed and the Mire's density to slow the creature, focusing only on getting back to the surface exit. [/INST] <s> **Narrator:** You choose to **Trigger the Barricade** as you retreat. Without breaking stride, you pivot slightly, sighting the flimsy barricade of pipe and remains. You fire the steam-pistol, not at the cultist remains, but at a crucial, rusted support bracket above the blockage. [SYSTEM: [ROLL LOG: Precision Shot Check: 7/10. **Success.** Structural collapse achieved.]] The bracket snaps, and the heavy piping and rubble, aided by the sticky weight of the Cultist's corpse, **collapses** in a chaotic, sludge-splattering mess, sealing the fissure with toxic debris. You hear the Mire-Gorgon\u2019s enraged bellow echo from the maintenance bay. The obstruction will not hold the creature for long, but the initial shock and the debris will buy you precious time. You **Continue Retreat** through the churning mire, the recovered data-slate clutched tightly in your uninjured hand. You crash out of the main tunnel and onto the solidified bank outside just as a tremendous *CRACK* signals the Gorgon has broken through the first layer of debris. You are exposed, but on solid ground, with the schematic secured. The mission is complete, but you are wounded and depleted. *** ### In-Lore Mission Report (Summary) **Mission Title:** The Scavenge of the Sunken City (Sector 9) **Character:** Uzman Engineer Kahlid **Faction:** Iron Sultanate (Uzman Corps) **Location:** The Brackish Mire, Sector 9, Western Reach **Objective:** Recover pre-war Sultanate Schematic Data-Slate. **Outcome:** **Success / Severe Wear** **Summary:** Engineer Kahlid successfully navigated the mire, neutralizing three aggressive Cannibal Cultists via decisive close-quarters and steam-pistol combat. The schematic was recovered from the sunken maintenance bay, despite the emergence of a large, hostile Mire-Gorgon. Kahlid successfully distracted the predator and caused a tunnel collapse to ensure extraction. Kahlid's armor sustained damage and he lost essential spare parts, but the Data-Slate ($XEN-790$) is secured and intact. **Uzman resources expended. Schematic recovered.** </s>"}
